{{Infobox Officeholder | name = Fong Chi Keong | native_name = {{nobold|馮志強}} | native_name_lang = zh-hant | honorific-suffix = [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Macau|OMIC]] | image = | caption = | order = | office = Member of the [[Legislative Assembly of Macau|Legislative Assembly]] | constituency = [[Functional constituency (Macau)|Business (FC)]] | predecessor = [[Hoi Sai Iun]] | successor = | term_start = 20 September 2009 | term_end = | constituency2 = [[Geographical constituency (Macau)|Macau (Directly elected)]] | predecessor2 = [[Jorge Manuel Fão]] | successor2 = [[Melinda Chan]] | term_start2 = 25 September 2005 | term_end2 = 20 September 2009 | constituency3 = [[Functional constituency (Macau)|Welfare, Culture, Education and Sport (FC)]] | predecessor3 = | successor3 = [[Jorge Manuel Fão]] | term_start3 = 23 September 2001 | term_end3 = 25 September 2005 | constituency4 = [[Geographical constituency (Macau)|Macau (Directly elected)]] | predecessor4 = | successor4 = [[Vitor Cheung]] | term_start4 = 3 October 1996 | term_end4 = 23 September 2001 | nationality = [[People's Republic of China|China]] | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1947|11|16}} | birth_place = [[Macau]] | death_date = | death_place = | spouse = | party = | religion = }} '''Fong Chi Keong''' ({{zh|t=馮志強}}; born 16 November 1947 in [[Macau]]<ref>{{cite journal |journal=澳門行政暨公職局 |date=2009-07-15 |title=第四屆立法會選舉候選名單總 |url=http://www.eal.gov.mo/2009/news/20090715.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090806210614/http://www.eal.gov.mo/2009/news/20090715.pdf |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2009-08-06 |df= }}</ref>) is a member of the [[Legislative Assembly of Macau]] and a businessman. Fong Chi Keong is known for criticism of the government and the [[New Macau Association]]. Fong Chi Keong often known as "Fong(Firing) Cannon" (馮大炮) for his radical talking in AL.
