'''Durnovo''' ''({{lang-ru|Дурново}})'' ''(known variant 'Durnovy' [plural], 'Durnov'[m] ,'Durnova' [f] ({{lang-ru|'Дурновы'; 'Дурнов', 'Дурнова'}}))'' is a prominent family of [[Russian nobility]]. '''Durnovo''' is one of two Russian noble families, of which the most famous is the branch of the [[Tolstoy (family)|'''Tolstoy''']] ({{lang-ru|Толсто́й}}).

In the mid 15th century The [[Velvet Book]] lists founder [[Mikula F. Durnovo]] ''({{lang-ru|Микула Фёдорович Дурново}})'' grandson of [[Vasily Yurevich Tolstoy]] ({{lang-ru|Василий Юрьевич Толстой}}), nicknamed as Durnoy ''({{lang-ru|Дурной}})'' ''[Could be translates as: A Fool, Spoiled, Bad, Joker])'' as a founder of the family. His brothers Daniel ''({{lang-ru|Данила}})'' and Basil ''({{lang-ru|Василий}})'' founded families of [[Danilov (dynasty)|Danilov]] ''({{lang-ru|Даниловы}})'' and [[Vasilchikov (dynasty)|Vasilchikov]] ''({{lang-ru|Васильчиковы}})''. 
Durnovo listed in the sixth part of the [[Gosudarev Rodoslovets|Sovereign's Pedigree Book]] of [[Vologda]], [[Kaluga]], [[Kostroma]], [[Moscow]], [[Oryol|Orёl]], and [[St. Petersburg]], [[Tambov]], [[Tula Oblast|Tula]] and [[Tver]] provinces.

==Coat of arms==
Durnovo’s coat of arms is practically identical with the "parent" coat of arms of [[Tolstoy (family)|Tolstoy]] family

