'''Pierre Brejoux''' was Inspector General of the Appellation d'Origine Controlee Board, which controls the production of top [[French wine]]s. he served as an expert wine taster in the [[Judgment of Paris (wine)|Paris Wine Tasting of 1976]]. In the [[blind tasting]], [[California wine]]s won both the red  and white wine categories. After the tasting, there were many calls for him to resign his position as Inspector General because so many people and groups were highly displeased with the results.  He is also the author of several books on French wine.

