'''ʿAbbāsa''' was the sister of the caliph [[Harun al-Rashid]] and [[Al-Hadi]], and daughter of the caliph [[Al-Mahdi]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url = http://referenceworks.brillonline.com/entries/encyclopaedia-of-islam-2/abba-sa-SIM_0031?s.num=24&s.rows=100|title = ʿAbbāsa." Encyclopaedia of Islam, Second Edition.|date = 26 March 2015|accessdate = 26 March 2015|website = Brillonline|publisher = Brill|last = Horovitz|first = J}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite book|title = The Caliph's Sister: Harun al-Rashid and the Fall of the Persians|last = Zaidan|first = Jurji|publisher = Zaidan Foundation|year = 2012|isbn = 0984843515|location = |pages = }}</ref> On the instruction of Harun al-Rashid she had a formal marriage with [[Ja'far ibn Yahya]], a member of the influential [[Barmakids]] family and vizier to the caliph.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /> Horovitz says that her name is connected with the fall of the Barmakids.<ref name=":0" />

